Police have arrested Abathembu King Dalindyebo. Eastern Cape SAPS spokesperson Brigadier Thembinkosi Kinana joins us on the line for more details. Courtesy #DStv403 PORT ELIZABETH - AbaThembu king Buyelekhaya Dalindyebo has been arrested on charges of malicious damage to property and assault in the early hours of Friday morning. READ: AbaThembu king qualifies for reduced sentence SAPS spokesperson Brigadier Thembinkosi Kinana confirmed the arrest and said the charges were laid by a family member. Dalindyebo will remain in police custody until he appears in court. READ: Dalindyebo won't resume royal duties just yet Dalindyebo was serving parole after qualifying for a remission of his 12-year sentence announced by President Cyril Ramaphosa last year. He had been convicted for assault with the intent to do grievous bodily harm, kidnapping, defeating the ends of justice, and arson. He was released in December after spending four years in prison.